# PaintBench environment template — copy to .env and fill in.
# .env itself is gitignored.

# ─── Image-editing API models ────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Used by nano-banana-1, nano-banana-2 (NanoBanana2Model), gpt-image-2.
# Precedence inside the model classes:
#   CLI flag > <ENV_KEY>_<NAME> env > GEMINI_<NAME> env > class default

# GEMINI_API_KEY=...
# GOOGLE_API_KEY=...

# Optional gateway override (e.g. an OpenAI-compatible passthrough). When
# set, the SDK uses Generative Language API mode rather than Vertex AI.
# GEMINI_BASE_URL=https://your-gateway.example/google/v1

# Per-variant overrides (NB1_*, NB2_*) let one .env route both Nano Banana
# variants through the same gateway while the model id differs per registry
# entry. Drop these if you're running with the canonical Google model IDs.
# NB1_MODEL_NAME=
# NB2_MODEL_NAME=
# NB1_INCLUDE_THOUGHTS=0       # NB1 (Gemini 2.5 Flash Image) rejects thinking_config
# NB2_INCLUDE_THOUGHTS=1

# OpenAI Images API (gpt-image-2)
# OPENAI_API_KEY=...

# ─── HuggingFace authentication (gated repos + private buckets) ──────────────
# Needed for `flux1-kontext-dev` and `flux2-klein-9b` (gated HF repos).
# HF_TOKEN=...
